he development of a new genre of Christian poetry. And, he examines anew Paulinus's relationships with such figures as Jerome, Rufinus, and Augustine. Trout fully explores the complexity of a figure who has too often been simplified and provides new insights into the kaleidoscopic character of the age in which he lived.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aChristian poetry, LatinxHistory and criticism. 0aChristian saintsxBiographyxItalyxNola. 0aChristian saintsxCorrespondencexItalyxNola. 0aChristian saintszItalyzNolavBiography. 0aChristian saintszItalyzNolavCorrespondence. 0aChristian saintszItalyzNolaxCorrespondence. 0aChristianity and literaturexRome. 0aChristianity and literaturezRome. 0aPoets, LatinxBiographyxItalyxNola. 0aPoets, LatinxCorrespondencexItalyxNola. 0aPoets, LatinzItalyzNolavBiography. 0aPoets, LatinzItalyzNolavCorrespondence. 0aPoets, LatinzItalyzNolaxBiography. 0aPoets, LatinzItalyzNolaxCorrespondence. 4aAncient Archaeology. 4aAncient History. 4aChristianity. 4aNear and Middle Eastern History. 4aOvid. 4aclassical literature. 4acomplexity. 4ahistory of art. 4ahistory of religion. 4ahistory. 4alifestyle. 4aliterature. 4amilitary history. 4aphilosophy of religion. 4aphilosophy. 4apolitical history. 4apolitical philosophy. 4apolitical science. 4apolitical theory. 4areligion. 4areligions of the ancient world. 4athe arts. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520922327?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520922327423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520922327/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles